            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-01-05T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-31T23:30:00-05:00" n="498" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In a cablegram dated March 1, Mr. Bunche advised that the Egyptian garrison of
                    2,900 men at al-Faluja, with their military equipment and personal possessions,
                    had been evacuated across the Egyptian border, pursuant to Article 3 of the
                    Egyptian-Israeli armistice agreement. The text of his communication is printed
                    in United Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official Records of the Security Council,
                        Fourth Tear, Supplement for March 1949</hi>, page 7. Hereinafter, these
                    official records will be identified as <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">4th yr</hi>., with indication of date of supplement.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
